text: {| |} The DeltaHawk DH160 is an American aircraft engine, under development by DeltaHawk Engines, Inc. of Racine, Wisconsin and intended for use in light aircraft.Bayerl, Robby; Martin Berkemeier; et al: World Directory of Leisure Aviation 2011-12, pages 238-239. WDLA UK, Lancaster UK, 2011. ISSN 1368-485X == Design and development == The engine is a four-cylinder two-stroke, V-layout, liquid-cooled, direct-drive, diesel engine design, which is intended to produce . The company intended to complete Federal Aviation Administration type certification , but did not achieve their goal. ==Specifications (DH160) == == See also == == References == == External links == * Category:DeltaHawk aircraft engines Category:2010s aircraft piston engines Category:Aircraft diesel engines
